1
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:33,166
[MISAKA WORST gasps]

2
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:42,875
[MISAKA WORST]
The bleeding has stopped.

3
00:00:42,958 --> 00:00:44,250
But why?

4
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:46,625
Misaka should not have
survived that attack.

5
00:00:50,958 --> 00:00:52,000
Impossible!

6
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:54,083
There's no way he
would save Misaka!

7
00:00:57,541 --> 00:00:59,791
What's wrong? [grunts]

8
00:00:59,875 --> 00:01:02,541
What reason do you have
to protect this Misaka?!

9
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:07,000
[MISAKA WORST yells, grunts]

10
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:23,500
[ACCELERATOR laughing]

11
00:03:12,208 --> 00:03:13,666
Vento.

12
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:17,541
It's Fiamma. I don't like the
way he does things. Period.

13
00:03:17,625 --> 00:03:19,666
He seemed to disappear
quite suddenly.

14
00:03:19,750 --> 00:03:21,083
Do you know where he went?

15
00:03:21,166 --> 00:03:22,125
Yeah.

16
00:03:23,166 --> 00:03:24,708
I have a pretty good guess.

17
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:39,583
Maybe you've convinced yourself
that you're not doing it

18
00:03:39,666 --> 00:03:41,666
for your own self-satisfaction.

19
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,250
But when all is said and done,

20
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:46,458
will your hypothetically noble
act actually be her salvation?

21
00:03:46,541 --> 00:03:48,958
I can't wait for the
judgment to come down.

22
00:03:50,166 --> 00:03:51,458
[LESSAR] I can't tell
what you're hiding,

23
00:03:51,541 --> 00:03:53,250
but whatever it is...

24
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,416
Remember that you didn't
stop dead in your tracks

25
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,583
when difficult
situations came up.

26
00:03:57,666 --> 00:03:59,625
You still continued to
move forward and give it

27
00:03:59,708 --> 00:04:01,875
everything you had,
no matter what.

28
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:05,916
And as a result, you've saved
a number of people's lives.

29
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,208
Take some credit.

30
00:04:07,291 --> 00:04:09,041
I mean, you even managed
to stop the coup

31
00:04:09,125 --> 00:04:10,416
back in Britain.

32
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,458
What I'm saying is
you've lived a life

33
00:04:12,541 --> 00:04:15,041
that you can be proud of.

34
00:04:15,125 --> 00:04:16,958
That's nice of you.

35
00:04:17,041 --> 00:04:18,000
But...

36
00:04:19,208 --> 00:04:20,833
...whatever my intentions
may have been,

37
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:23,583
the decisions I made
affected Index.

38
00:04:23,666 --> 00:04:25,083
And the fact is...

39
00:04:25,166 --> 00:04:27,750
I'm not the one who gets to
decide what's best for her.

40
00:04:36,916 --> 00:04:38,583
[TANK DRIVER 20A chuckling]

41
00:04:38,666 --> 00:04:40,333
Just keep on running!

42
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,083
[CHILD 19A gasps]

43
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,291
[CITIZEN 19A, CHILD 19A gasp]

44
00:04:54,375 --> 00:04:56,208
[HAMAZURA yelling]

45
00:04:58,458 --> 00:05:01,166
[yelling]

46
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:06,041
Go! Now!

47
00:05:08,416 --> 00:05:09,791
I'm sorry.

48
00:05:09,875 --> 00:05:11,458
I hate that I'm the one who
dragged you into all this.

49
00:05:11,541 --> 00:05:13,791
Now is not a good
time for apologies!

50
00:05:13,875 --> 00:05:15,833
Besides, you've given
Takitsubo a spot

51
00:05:15,916 --> 00:05:17,375
in your underground shelter.

52
00:05:17,458 --> 00:05:18,875
Consider this payback.

53
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:40,000
[HAMAZURA]
Why're they stopping?

54
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:41,166
They're not.

55
00:05:46,333 --> 00:05:48,166
[HAMAZURA, DIGURV grunting]

56
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:57,166
They really do enjoy
killing people, don't they?

57
00:05:57,250 --> 00:06:00,791
At this rate, everyone in the
village will be dead soon.

58
00:06:00,875 --> 00:06:02,125
[HAMAZURA]
Not if we can help it.

59
00:06:05,291 --> 00:06:06,583
Weapons.

60
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:09,000
Don't you have anything
stored away for emergencies?

61
00:06:09,083 --> 00:06:10,541
We don't have anything
that would cut through

62
00:06:10,625 --> 00:06:12,833
that kind of armor.

63
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:15,166
I think you do!

64
00:06:15,250 --> 00:06:16,416
The landmines.

65
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,000
You said you were
saving them so you could

66
00:06:18,083 --> 00:06:20,333
turn them over to an NGO, right?

67
00:06:25,791 --> 00:06:27,916
[KNIGHT LEADER]
Can we really hold the line?

68
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,250
[CARISSA] I wouldn't exactly
call this a defensive war

69
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:31,708
of attrition.

70
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:34,333
It's more of a mop-up battle
to prepare for our attack.

71
00:06:39,708 --> 00:06:42,625
Glastonbury,
the mobile fortress.

72
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:47,375
By taking control of the area
around it and claiming it

73
00:06:47,458 --> 00:06:50,833
as British territory,
we are able to dramatically

74
00:06:50,916 --> 00:06:53,333
extend Curtana's range of usage.

75
00:06:57,958 --> 00:07:01,708
And it truly is a larger-scale
magical item for invasions.

76
00:07:01,791 --> 00:07:04,083
The intent of the enemy doesn't
even matter in this case,

77
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:05,750
don't you agree?

78
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:07,541
Yes.

79
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:09,875
[CARISSA] There's one
more thing I'd like to try.

80
00:07:10,958 --> 00:07:11,916
[yells]

81
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,291
Somebody please help me!

82
00:07:13,375 --> 00:07:14,875
If those evil
French bastards win,

83
00:07:14,958 --> 00:07:18,208
I'll be captured and
violated before I die!

84
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:21,291
[BRITISH SORCERERS yelling]

85
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:24,625
We must keep
Princess Carissa safe!

86
00:07:24,708 --> 00:07:27,041
That's more like it. Where
was this kind of enthusiasm

87
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:28,416
when you first
started fighting?

88
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:29,791
[KNIGHT LEADER]
That's right.

89
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:31,833
Could you please put me
in touch with Queen Elizard?

90
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:33,333
As soon as possible.

91
00:07:33,416 --> 00:07:36,041
I want to ask her permission
to punish Princess Carissa.

92
00:07:36,125 --> 00:07:38,000
[CARISSA]
What do you think you're doing?

93
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:40,166
Come on, you know
how my mother can be.

94
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:42,833
She would probably bestow
all of Curtana Second's power

95
00:07:42,916 --> 00:07:44,791
to you just so you
could humiliate me.

96
00:07:44,875 --> 00:07:46,375
[FEMME FATALE]
Second Princess Carissa?

97
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:47,833
I thought that was you.

98
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,541
It's The holy maiden
of Versailles.

99
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:01,750
[CARISSA] Your body has
undergone conditioning

100
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:03,916
at the visceral level.

101
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,666
It's prevented you
from being able to live

102
00:08:05,750 --> 00:08:07,916
outside the confines
of Versailles.

103
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:10,750
Your power's been curtailed
by idiotic French heavyweights

104
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:12,375
who fear you.

105
00:08:12,458 --> 00:08:14,166
Therefore, victory is ours!

106
00:08:14,250 --> 00:08:16,166
If you were able to
come out here directly,

107
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:18,250
the battle might have
ended differently.

108
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:19,625
[FEMME FATALE chuckles]

109
00:08:22,166 --> 00:08:23,208
[CARISSA grunts]

110
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:32,166
[FEMME FATALE] Actually,
I am able to move about.

111
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:35,916
And that will become known as
France's mightiest move to date.

112
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:41,583
[KANZAKI gasps]

113
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:46,875
What's that?

114
00:08:48,458 --> 00:08:50,750
Don't tell me you're wielding a
fragment of Curtana Second!

115
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,750
It's a result of
my fight with Mother.

116
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:55,208
During which, Curtana
Original and Curtana Second

117
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:58,666
endured a heavy-handed clash,
and this is the result.

118
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:01,958
Like you, I am also
free to move about,

119
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:04,833
and that is the greatest
move Britain ever made!

120
00:09:08,375 --> 00:09:10,625
--[KAMIJO grunts]
--[LESSAR] What the--?

121
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:12,291
[DRIVER 20A]
Look! Over there!

122
00:09:16,583 --> 00:09:19,125
[ACCELERATOR laughing]

123
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:21,666
That's it! I
can't hold it in any longer!

124
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:24,083
It's gonna take more than
that kid's precious smile

125
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:25,666
to stop it now!

126
00:09:27,416 --> 00:09:32,916
[laughing]

127
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,250
I wanna see every last
inch of it destroyed!

128
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:36,333
[laughing]

129
00:09:36,416 --> 00:09:38,833
I wanna mow down
everything in existence!

130
00:09:38,916 --> 00:09:40,833
[laughing]

131
00:09:40,916 --> 00:09:43,083
I want to rid this world
of people who would create

132
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:44,291
such a thing!

133
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:46,666
Put an end to the jerks
who benefit from it.

134
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,250
Forever!

135
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,958
And I mean all of them!

136
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:53,166
Every last disgusting one!
[laughing]

137
00:09:53,250 --> 00:09:54,625
[KAMIJO]
Accelerator!

138
00:09:59,458 --> 00:10:00,625
No way.

139
00:10:00,708 --> 00:10:02,041
Why're you here?

140
00:10:03,791 --> 00:10:06,291
Tell me. Tell me!

141
00:10:06,375 --> 00:10:08,541
Tell me why!

142
00:10:17,166 --> 00:10:19,916
Well, if it isn't the so-called
hero who gave enough of a damn

143
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,458
to save all those sisters.

144
00:10:21,541 --> 00:10:24,125
What the hell are
you talking about?

145
00:10:24,208 --> 00:10:26,750
[ACCELERATOR]
But what about the kid, huh?

146
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,708
She's never done
anything to hurt anyone

147
00:10:28,791 --> 00:10:31,125
in her entire existence!

148
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:33,458
So what sense does it
make for someone like her

149
00:10:33,541 --> 00:10:35,708
to suffer like that?!

150
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:39,166
[yelling]

151
00:10:43,333 --> 00:10:44,291
[KAMIJO grunts]

152
00:10:52,291 --> 00:10:53,833
[LESSAR whimpering]

153
00:10:53,916 --> 00:10:55,041
[KAMIJO yells]

154
00:11:15,791 --> 00:11:17,333
[TANK DRIVER 20A laughs]

155
00:11:17,416 --> 00:11:19,500
Where are you hiding,
little kitties?

156
00:11:19,583 --> 00:11:21,833
Come out, come out,
wherever you are!

157
00:11:21,916 --> 00:11:23,208
[laughs]

158
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,958
We don't know which
route they're using,

159
00:11:51,041 --> 00:11:53,333
and there's not a lot
of time to set things up.

160
00:11:57,125 --> 00:11:58,666
[HAMAZURA]
There's not much else we can do.

161
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:00,958
So toss them like grenades
when they get close.

162
00:12:15,083 --> 00:12:16,875
Oh, you're heading
my way first, are you?

163
00:12:16,958 --> 00:12:18,291
That's fine with me!

164
00:12:19,791 --> 00:12:21,375
I'm ready for it.

165
00:12:21,458 --> 00:12:23,250
Come at me any way you like!

166
00:12:28,791 --> 00:12:29,750
[HAMAZURA grunts]

167
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:39,791
[DIGURV]
Did that do it?

168
00:12:45,041 --> 00:12:46,500
[PRIVATEER DRIVER 20A]
Damn it, move!

169
00:12:49,541 --> 00:12:51,333
[HAMAZURA]
It's chilly out today, huh?

170
00:12:51,416 --> 00:12:53,875
That's my favorite kind of
weather for a barbecue.

171
00:13:04,875 --> 00:13:06,000
It's not over.

172
00:13:12,375 --> 00:13:14,583
[PRIVATEER PILOT 20A laughs]

173
00:13:14,666 --> 00:13:16,750
I'll blast ya full of holes!

174
00:13:19,208 --> 00:13:20,416
Damn it!

175
00:13:57,541 --> 00:14:02,041
[ACCELERATOR laughing]

176
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:07,375
[ACCELERATOR laughs]

177
00:14:10,458 --> 00:14:13,416
[KAMIJO yelling]

178
00:14:17,750 --> 00:14:19,083
[KAMIJO yelling]

179
00:14:31,291 --> 00:14:32,583
[KAMIJO yelling]

180
00:14:33,875 --> 00:14:37,416
[ACCELERATOR yelling]

181
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,541
You're supposed
to be the big hero!

182
00:14:39,625 --> 00:14:41,625
If you've got special
powers no one else has,

183
00:14:41,708 --> 00:14:43,083
then share the damn wealth!

184
00:14:43,166 --> 00:14:45,458
Why not use some to
help that kid, huh?!

185
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:51,000
How crazy is it that a
villainous bastard like me

186
00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:52,583
is the only one who's
ever cared enough

187
00:14:52,666 --> 00:14:54,166
to stick up for her
all this time?

188
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:57,208
Just look at me! There's
no way I could be a hero!

189
00:14:57,291 --> 00:14:59,500
I don't save anyone! Ever!

190
00:14:59,583 --> 00:15:01,500
When I wanna fix something,

191
00:15:01,583 --> 00:15:04,250
I do it with blood and pain!

192
00:15:04,333 --> 00:15:06,250
I shouldn't have to
go through this crap!

193
00:15:06,333 --> 00:15:07,666
You're the damn hero!

194
00:15:07,750 --> 00:15:10,458
It's your job to
rush to the rescue!

195
00:15:10,541 --> 00:15:11,833
[ACCELERATOR coughs]

196
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:19,791
If damn heroes would
do their job and show up

197
00:15:19,875 --> 00:15:22,166
when they're supposed to,
stupid mistakes like this

198
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:24,875
never would've been
possible in the first place!

199
00:15:24,958 --> 00:15:26,541
That kid might be okay!

200
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:28,541
If you had been there,
she wouldn't have had to

201
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:29,916
suffer like that!

202
00:15:48,875 --> 00:15:51,208
You're kidding me.
What the hell?!

203
00:15:51,291 --> 00:15:53,708
Hero or not,
that should've killed you!

204
00:15:53,791 --> 00:15:56,125
[KAMIJO]
What's a hero to you anyway?

205
00:15:56,208 --> 00:15:58,541
An average Level Zero like me?

206
00:15:58,625 --> 00:16:01,500
Do I really look like I'm
that big of a deal to anyone?

207
00:16:02,583 --> 00:16:04,666
Good guys? Bad guys?

208
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:06,166
Come on, grow up!

209
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:08,916
Are you saying that
in order to help someone,

210
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,708
you have to meet
specific qualifications?

211
00:16:11,791 --> 00:16:14,708
If someone you know is crying
and you wish they weren't,

212
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:17,291
or if someone struggling
to hold on needs help

213
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:20,125
but doesn't have
the strength to ask...

214
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:22,291
Isn't that reason enough?

215
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:24,125
What more do you
need to step up?

216
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:27,250
You want special permission
or some kind of label?

217
00:16:27,333 --> 00:16:29,500
It's no skin off your
nose to try and help.

218
00:16:29,583 --> 00:16:31,708
If they're important,
what's stopping you?

219
00:16:32,916 --> 00:16:34,083
[ACCELERATOR grunts]

220
00:16:34,833 --> 00:16:36,541
[grunts]

221
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:38,708
I don't know what it is
you're afraid of or how badly

222
00:16:38,791 --> 00:16:40,750
you've been burned
by others in the past,

223
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:42,416
but if you wanted
to protect that kid,

224
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:45,208
then you should've just done
so with your head held high!

225
00:16:46,500 --> 00:16:48,541
You have the strength
and ability to keep her safe

226
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:50,791
right now!
Be proud of that!

227
00:16:55,958 --> 00:16:56,916
[KAMIJO grunts]

228
00:17:11,291 --> 00:17:13,166
[KAMIJO]
The choice is yours.

229
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:15,958
You can continue protecting
her on your own.

230
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:18,791
You can run away and
leave it for someone else.

231
00:17:18,875 --> 00:17:22,416
Or you can ask for help
and we can do this together!

232
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,666
[ACCELERATOR]
I don't--

233
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:25,791
I am not going to make
this decision for you.

234
00:17:25,875 --> 00:17:28,458
Call it arrogance or
whatever you want.

235
00:17:28,541 --> 00:17:31,125
You're the only one who can
decide if she's worth it.

236
00:17:31,208 --> 00:17:33,250
No one else can
tell you what to do!

237
00:17:39,208 --> 00:17:41,125
[ACCELERATOR]
I wanted to defend her.

238
00:17:41,208 --> 00:17:43,833
No matter the cost.

239
00:17:43,916 --> 00:17:45,875
I had to do something.

240
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:49,416
So I rushed down the only
path I knew I could take.

241
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:53,708
I chose the path of evil, and I
excelled at living that life.

242
00:17:56,083 --> 00:17:57,083
However...

243
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:15,333
In the end, it was the guy
who never once had to question

244
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:18,208
whether he was good or evil
who managed to come through.

245
00:18:18,291 --> 00:18:20,750
Turned out that he was
the strongest one of all.

246
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:24,666
I can't protect her
with pure evil.

247
00:18:32,708 --> 00:18:35,500
Fighting for those suffering
from inexcusable savagery.

248
00:18:35,583 --> 00:18:38,458
And giving everything you have
to stop unnecessary tears.

249
00:18:38,541 --> 00:18:41,625
These are what I would call
very admirable actions, indeed.

250
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:43,708
[PRIVATEER PILOTS gasp]

251
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,583
[ACQUA]
I am Aqua of the Rear.

252
00:19:03,666 --> 00:19:06,375
May I be so presumptuous
as to offer you a hand?

253
00:19:07,333 --> 00:19:10,000
[weapons clash]

254
00:19:10,083 --> 00:19:11,458
What did you just say?

255
00:19:11,541 --> 00:19:13,041
[CARISSA]
The Kremlin Report.

256
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,958
It's Russia's first-priority
national defense manual.

257
00:19:17,041 --> 00:19:19,083
If the mainland is
invaded by force,

258
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:21,041
and the nuclear launch
facilities are about to be

259
00:19:21,125 --> 00:19:22,250
taken over,

260
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:24,333
do you have any idea
what means they'll adopt

261
00:19:24,416 --> 00:19:26,666
in order to prevent
that from happening?

262
00:19:26,750 --> 00:19:27,833
Give up?

263
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:29,791
They'll disperse a
bacterial wall to act

264
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:32,000
as an airborne killer!

265
00:19:32,083 --> 00:19:34,833
There won't be a single
evacuation order issued.

266
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:37,750
Not for the Russian soldiers
who are working in the facility,

267
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:39,541
or the people who live nearby.

268
00:19:39,625 --> 00:19:42,208
The manual's sole priority
is to ensure the security

269
00:19:42,291 --> 00:19:43,958
of the nuclear launch sites.

270
00:19:44,041 --> 00:19:45,750
It doesn't matter how
many times you brag

271
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,458
about how just your cause is.

272
00:19:47,541 --> 00:19:49,750
The fact remains that
you're using French soil

273
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:52,291
as a springboard to
intervene in Russia.

274
00:19:52,375 --> 00:19:54,416
France has enjoyed
many benefits from growth

275
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:56,916
under the protection of
the Roman Orthodox Church.

276
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,250
So now we can't afford to
cast aside their orders.

277
00:19:59,333 --> 00:20:01,500
Everyone knows the
truth about this war.

278
00:20:01,583 --> 00:20:03,500
We're all very much aware
that it wasn't caused

279
00:20:03,583 --> 00:20:05,791
by the Roman Orthodoxy,
but by Fiamma.

280
00:20:07,875 --> 00:20:09,583
And now we have the
opportunity to avoid

281
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:11,625
a worst-case scenario.

282
00:20:11,708 --> 00:20:13,166
So what'll it be?

283
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:15,125
You know, there was a time
when I considered France

284
00:20:15,208 --> 00:20:16,708
to be my archenemy.

285
00:20:16,791 --> 00:20:19,750
Hard to believe they can really
be this pathetic and useless.

286
00:20:24,041 --> 00:20:25,125
[KUROKO]
Hey, Sissy!

287
00:20:28,291 --> 00:20:29,250
[KUROKO]
Look!

288
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:35,500
Wait, why are you packing?

289
00:20:37,750 --> 00:20:40,041
[KUROKO] Can you at least
tell me what your plan is?

290
00:20:40,125 --> 00:20:41,583
You're not going there, are you?

291
00:20:41,666 --> 00:20:42,625
Uh...

292
00:20:44,041 --> 00:20:45,458
But why? It's a war zone.

293
00:20:45,541 --> 00:20:47,250
And how do you even
expect to get in?

294
00:20:47,333 --> 00:20:49,250
Oh. Um... Well...

295
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:50,500
There are ways.

296
00:20:54,083 --> 00:20:57,958
[MUGINO humming]

297
00:20:58,041 --> 00:21:02,333
I can't wait to see
you again, Hamazura.

298
00:21:21,208 --> 00:21:23,875
[ACCELERATOR]
"Index Librorum Prohibitorum." 

299
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:30,333
Welcome to the Elizalina
Alliance of Independent Nations.

300
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:35,291
[ACCELERATOR] Maybe it is
all connected somehow.

301
00:21:38,291 --> 00:21:41,083
[KAMIJO] I was probably too
hard on Accelerator back there.

302
00:21:41,166 --> 00:21:43,541
I don't get shuffling around
looking for a logical reason

303
00:21:43,625 --> 00:21:44,916
to help.

304
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,125
I don't do it
because it's right.

305
00:21:47,208 --> 00:21:50,083
The only reason I helped
her is because I wanted to.

306
00:21:50,166 --> 00:21:51,666
[LESSAR laughs]

307
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:54,208
One minute you're stressed out,
and the next you bounce back!

308
00:21:54,291 --> 00:21:56,000
That must keep you pretty busy.

309
00:21:58,500 --> 00:22:01,041
[KAMIJO] I realize that
I'm a real lowlife.

310
00:22:01,125 --> 00:22:03,666
I'm a worthless jerk who's
been deceiving Index.

311
00:22:05,416 --> 00:22:08,041
But as bad as I may be,

312
00:22:08,125 --> 00:22:12,041
I know for sure it's not
Fiamma I should be bowing to.

313
00:22:15,833 --> 00:22:17,291
Well, now.

314
00:22:17,375 --> 00:22:19,500
I'd say it's a perfect time
to begin the delightful

315
00:22:19,583 --> 00:22:21,250
Project B'Tselem.

316
00:23:56,708 --> 00:23:58,625
[KAMIJO]
The project kicks off at last.

317
00:23:58,708 --> 00:24:01,125
The earth shakes,
the skies turn pitch-black,

318
00:24:01,208 --> 00:24:03,208
and strange objects rise.

319
00:24:03,291 --> 00:24:05,416
The light of
destruction descends.

320
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:07,583
Next time,
"The Star of Bethlehem."

321
00:24:07,666 --> 00:24:10,458
When science and magic cross
paths, a story is born.

